    <item>
      <title>Rogue DPS concerns... trying to think outside the box</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=roguebalance&amp;message.id=4623#M4623</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face="Times New Roman"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face="Times New Roman"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;font face="Times New Roman"&gt;&lt;font color="#ffffff"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Trying to think outside of the box when it comes to ways to improve rogue dps and other class specific issues. While thinking outside of the box I am trying to remain as objective as possible in regards to the impact the “suggestions” would have and how viable they are in the context of the entire game and all the other classes. But hey… I’m a rogue, there is always a chance what I view as viable is viewed by another as overpowered, idiotic, etc…&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;1.New upgraded version of our Blinding Speed (lvl 58) discipline – 25-30% overhaste for a duration of 1 minute. Recast timer of 1min 30seconds, Endurance cost around 800, Self only, uses the Thiefs Eye discipline model by populating buff icon in the short duration buff box (bard song box). Like Thiefs Eye it would allow us reap it’s benefits while using other disciplines but endurance cost is prohibitive enough that you can’t sustain it when you are not grouped with a bard. Overhaste does not stack with bard overhaste song. Gives rogues a little bit more burst dps for the times they aren’t grouped with a bard.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;2.Power Strike .. aka Endurance Burn – Rogue AA with 3 levels. Level 1 lets you do one single backstab strike at 1x your maximum endurance. Level 2 lets you do one single backstab strike at 1.5x your maximum endurance. Level 3 lets you do one single backstab strike at 2x your maximum endurance. Costs approximately 2500-3000 endurance with a refresh timer about the same as wizards/necros (2hr). The reason behind the lower comparative endurance cost compared to the cost that wizards/necros pay for their similar ability is because of the endurance regeneration disparity compared to mana and hp regen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;3.Position Liberation – modify the game mechanics to allow rogues to backstab: full damage full benefit from the 90deg rear arc, 80% damage full benefit from the two side 90deg arcs, frontal arc unaffected by this change but is still subject to the chaotic stab type rogue aa lines. From the side we would pay a 20% penalty to our backstab damage and still be subject to the normal mob-side rules (damageless riposte etc). Would bump up our position independent dps but still keep us slightly under position independent classes (monk/bst/zerk/ranger) in terms of return on investment for mob positioning. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;4.Offhand special attack – give rogues an offhand special attack(s) option that isn’t tied to normal attack or backstab. Lots of possible implementations here like 1) dps attack that gives an extra 15-20dps when used consistently. 2) a blackjack strike attack that does minimal dps but has a chance to interrupt casters with a 0 second stun (subject to corresponding agro from the stun of course). 3) a knee cap/tendon slice attack that does a short duration (1-2 ticks) snare (maybe 20% ?). All 3 special attacks on the same refresh timer so they are mutually exclusive of eachother. Possibly could even tie them to the weapon type the rogue is using in their offhand. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;5.Offhand flurry – innate or aa driven ability to flurry attack with the rogues offhand weapon&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;6.Offhand triple attack – either innate and tied to our double attack % or aa driven and a straight % chance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;7.Sweet Spot – disc or AA that when activated gets populated into the short duration buff bar (bard song box) that allows rogues a chance to avoid AE rampage damage when the rogue is within 10% of max melee range. If done as a disc give it a flat 50% chance to completely avoid ae rampage damage. If done as an AA make it 5 levels with 10-12% chance to completely avoid an AE rampage per level. Duration should be fairly lengthy as should the refresh timer, open to ideas on specific duration(s). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Any opinions?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Sun, 30 Apr 2006 02:53:19 GMT</pubDate>
