    <item>
      <title>Top 10 Discussion/Ideas thread.</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=roguebalance&amp;message.id=4585#M4585</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Recap, what is already on our top 10 as of current.&lt;br&gt;1) Boost Sustained DPS&lt;br&gt;- Boost sustained DPS through the addition of triple attack or via backstab accuracy or other damage increases so that we maintain a clear advantage over other classes in sustained DPS.&lt;br&gt;- At present, parses suggest that rogues do not have the highest sustained dps among the dps classes. Rogues sustained dps should be special. Rogues feel that their sustained dps should exceed that of every other class under most circumstances and by a significant margin.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;2) Disciplines / Burst DPS&lt;br&gt;- Move Assassin's Feint line off the Sneak Attack line timer.&lt;br&gt;- Move Twisted Chance to the Deadeye timer or its own timer. This discipline serves no purpose on its present timer.&lt;br&gt;- Add a new long duration discipline to boost burst dps.&lt;br&gt;- Re-evaluate the endurance costs of the Sneak Attack line.&lt;br&gt;- At present, parses suggest that in relation to many classes rogue dps is okay. However, a few classes are close enough to rogue dps and there are enough exceptions that rogues dps is no longer special, and according to parses one or more classes may be outperforming us in general. Rogues feel that their damage on raids should exceed every class bar wizards under most circumstances and by a significant margin. There are presently too many exceptions to the rule (see also: 7 - position dependancy). Under no circumstances should a tank class be competitive dps.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;3) Better Player Made Traps&lt;br&gt;- Design of player made traps needs some work still. Agro from traps should be minimal.&lt;br&gt;- Please replace rogues current trap.&lt;br&gt;- Rogues, masters of traps and masters of damage, are not satisfied with the trap they received. They should either receive a better selection of traps or they should receive a more useful aura.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;4) Modify the Backstab Formula&lt;br&gt;- Backstab hits for too little too often. Minimum backstab should be adjusted upwards or should occur less often.&lt;br&gt;- Backstab scaling should be more linear or be adjusted to allow for greater dagger upgrades.&lt;br&gt;- Gaining a part of a point of damage per expansion doesn't feel right, and eventually even elemental damage will be too much of an upgrade. Additionally, it would be nice if piercer ratios could be more akin to the ratios of other weapons (see also: 9 - Itemisation).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;5) Nerves of Steel&lt;br&gt;- At maximum ranks, a resisted, area effect spell can break Nerves of Steel. This is a bug. Please fix it.&lt;br&gt;- Although bugs shouldn't need to be on the top 10, this bug has remained unfixed for far too long.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;6) Shroud of Stealth&lt;br&gt;- Make it possible to identify mobs which see through SoS without conning them.&lt;br&gt;- There appear to be too many see-SoS mobs, particularly in instances.&lt;br&gt;- Zonewide AEs are increasingly common and break SoS for the entire zone.&lt;br&gt;- The &amp;quot;Your Shroud of Stealth keeps you hidden&amp;quot; message doesn't appear to be functioning properly. It's been suggested that this is because the message doesn't function on undead mobs.&lt;br&gt;- NPCs with whom players are supposed to talk in DoDH have helpfully been flagged as see-invis. They need to be flagged as see-SoS as well&lt;br&gt;- Shroud of Stealth needs to be highly reliable. Note that anywhere that a rogue could go with shroud of stealth, a bard or monk can already go.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;7) Position Dependancy / Backstab Failures&lt;br&gt;- Backstab failing due to Out of Range / Cannot See should not cause backstab / sneak attack to be greyed out.&lt;br&gt;- Too many raid targets are unpinnable or extremely difficult to pin with the result that rogue dps is becoming sub-par. Either more raid targets need to be pinnable / perma-rooted or rogue dps needs to be boosted to take the lost dps into account.&lt;br&gt;- Increase hitbox size of mobs, particularly on raid encounters&lt;br&gt;- Fix the &amp;quot;cannot see&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;out of range&amp;quot; issues with backstab. Suggested that this is caused by client/server syncing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;8) Poisons&lt;br&gt;Make poisons easier to use and less prohibitive in terms of time investment. Some suggestions of how to achieve this are:&lt;br&gt;- Implement some form of endless poison or poison conservation AA.&lt;br&gt;- Increase the drop rate of poison ingredients or make them purchaseable at a reasonable cost.&lt;br&gt;- Increase the yield of poisons per combine.&lt;br&gt;- Dramatically increase the yield of poisons per combine, making the poisons yielded no rent.&lt;br&gt;- Make old world and PoP poisons stackable&lt;br&gt;- Add a resist adjustment for poisons via AAs or new poison recipes.&lt;br&gt;- Implement new poison recipes.&lt;br&gt;- Poison skills have gone neglected for too long.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;9) Itemisation&lt;br&gt;- Add more +backstab damage items at all levels of play.&lt;br&gt;- Add more and better single groupable daggers to allow casual rogue dps to keep up with other classes.&lt;br&gt;- Itemisation at the high end needs to be more rewarding (drool-worthy) and play to rogues strengths.&lt;br&gt;- More variety in piercer graphics. If possible, try to avoid one dagger being a clear winner because inevitably everyone will end up wielding that dagger.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;10) AE Rampage&lt;br&gt;- Add an additional defence for rogues to avoid AE rampage.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Keep the Discussion clean please it makes my job easier if everybody isn't going at  eachother. feel free to post ideas for the top 10 list or suggestions for the current items.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!--   / message   --&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Thu, 25 May 2006 15:26:59 GMT</pubDate>
