    <item>
      <title>Suggestions on Rogue DPS</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=roguebalance&amp;message.id=4561#M4561</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;p&gt;First off I would like to start with that everyone please post positively in the goal of increasing our damage output. Please stay away from posting negative ideas about other classes, or posts saying just &amp;quot;X-class has it, so we should&amp;quot; give positive feedback in why we should have it. I hope if we can keep this thread with positive posts, the devolpers can take some ideas from it and implement them later. If you have any ideas, post them, the more ideas out there the better it can help out us and the devolpers. If you dont like an idea, then post in constructive criticism about why that ability would not help our class.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now remember on your ideas, devolpers do want to increase our dps. But they want to do it with moderation so we dont upset any other classes. So try not to do any outrageous ideas that would increase us by to much.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I would like to work off with ideas of our Top Ten to start us off.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;font face="Times New Roman"&gt;1) Boost Sustained DPS &lt;font face="Times New Roman" color="#ff0000"&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face="Times New Roman" color="#ffff00"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face="Times New Roman"&gt;- Boost sustained DPS by ~5% either through the addition of triple attack or via backstab accuracy or damage increases so that we maintain a clear advantage over other classes in sustained DPS.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;p&gt;Flurry - Would be a beneficial to the rogue class in increasing sustained damage output of the rogue class. Their are several classes with this ability and it increased their dps, but it wasnt a large increase to their class. Perfect to what our class needs&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Backstab Accuracy - With the mob's defense skills increasing, backstab is missing more and more. Backstab at lower levels had higher accuracy because skill and accuracy more matched the mobs defense. Increasing the accuracy of this skill landing would help both the raiding rogue and the casual playing rogue.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;p&gt;2) Disciplines / Burst DPS &lt;font face="Times New Roman" color="#ff0000"&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face="Times New Roman"&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Move Assassin's Feint line off the Sneak Attack line timer .&lt;br&gt;- Move Twisted Chance to the Deadeye timer or its own timer.&lt;br&gt;- Add a new long duration discipline to boost burst dps&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;p&gt;Assassin's Feint has no relation to the sneak attack line. Therefore it should be moved to a timer which does not conflict with that timer. Say if a rogue sneak attacks a mob, but then a mob the rogue wants to mez. But the rogue cannot do this action for 30 seconds. Which sets up a confliction of disciplines.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;p&gt;Discipline Timer 2:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/b&gt;Twisted Chance - Increase Chance to Critical Hit by 500%, Increase Chance to Hit by 10000% with All Skills&lt;br&gt;Duelist - Increase All Skills Damage Modifier by 100%, Increase All Skills Minimum Damage Modifier by 400%&lt;br&gt;Kinesthetics - Increase Dual Wield by 10000%, Increase Double Attack by 10000%&lt;b&gt;&lt;p&gt;Discipline Timer 3:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/b&gt;Deadly Precision - Increase Chance to Hit by 10000% with Backstab&lt;br&gt;Blinding Speed - Hundred Hands Effect&lt;br&gt;Deadeye - Increase Chance to Hit by 10000% with All Skills&lt;p&gt;Now if you look at all those disciplines, you can see a strong relationship with Deadeye, Deadly Precision, Kinesthetics, and Twisted Chance. So much to the fact that Twisted Chance is the direct upgrade to all of those disciplines (especially to Deadeye). With their strong relationship of those disciplines would be a just reason on why they should all share the same timer. Now if you look at the extra disciplines, you have Blinding Speed and Duelist. Since they have no relation to any other discipline they should either be put on the same timer, or on their own seperate timers and later on recieve upgrades to them. Especially since in future expansion the chances of level increase to level 75 would give plenty of level opportunity for upgrades of those disciplines. They are our current top disciplines used for us, and since they are both in the upper 50s, its time for them to recieve an upgrade. And I personally dont think having four offensive timers would overpower us, it would just offer more burst dps, but not anything to hurt other classes.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;As for a new long duration discipline, I do not feel we need this. But more a clickable offense alternative advancement ability. We are one of the few dps classes out there who do not recieve a clickable AA ability that helps our dps. Some examples I would like to suggest are:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Option #1: Accuracy and Attack, Short Duration (30 seconds to 60 seconds), Long Reuse (One hour)&lt;br&gt;Option #2: Poison Proc Buff, Long Duration (30 minutes to one hour), 100 damage to 200 damage proc, with a deagro jolt in it. Our evade ability has a strong chance of failure, so having an abiltiy like this would lower us from being on the top of hate lists. Which in the long run would help us be better damage output in group and raid situations.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I would like to point out to other rogues once again. Please post positive on ideas to help our class, do not feel intimidated on posting. All opinions count here, from casual to end game raiding. If you dont like someone's idea, post constructive criticism in why you dont like the idea. I feel if we all work together on coming up with good ideas. It would help the Sony Devolper Team to use our ideas in future patches and expansions.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by Gammak on &lt;span class="date_text"&gt;04-13-2006&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="time_text"&gt;12:29 AM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
