      <title>Gripes, Ideas and maybe even a rant;  Posted multipul places for your viewing pleasure</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=roguebalance&amp;message.id=4549#M4549</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;70 rogue Tunare. Just some background info. I have played every class to 60+ other then beastlord bard and berserker. Bards I have just not had time for and like to live under the illusion that they are complicated beyond my understanding. bls and zerkers are abominations and should be put down for the good of man kind. Im old school I hate frogs lizards and yes even you cats... although less then frogs I really hate frogs and halflings. Anyway I have some Ideas for our class i thought i would share.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Something I think that would help our overall dps our ability to survive and a bit of self utility anyway. Innate life/mana/end taps . Starting at lvl 50 scaling up to lvl 70. Nothing huge maybe 50/50/50 at lvl 70 with a typical lifetap resist mod so that its not going to get resisted often. To me this is the ultimate theft and right up our alley. I think it should have a fairly high proc rate maybe with aa to increase both frequency and effectiveness maybe an aa to crit with it I dont know tons of options. I know this maybe stepping on the toes of sks and necros but ya know what the He77 with them they are way to powerful to be complaining about us. I dont want to see this as a buff or an aa other then the possible aa to make it better but an Innate ability that all rogues get at said lvl.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If that seems unreasonable to have something innate make it a disc but with much more powerful taps like say 500lt proc over 30 seconds or 1 min again with a fairly high proc rate and resist mod. Make us once again not only the king of dps but the king of thieves &amp;quot;yes bad joke intended&amp;quot;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Weapons nothing makes me more upset then fighting with other classes over good weapons. Pure melee live and die by there weapons. The best weapons that are now available to classes like rangers, bards and beastlords should in the future NOT BE!! Pure melee monks war rogue should be the only ones to have access to the best melee weapons. The other classes have many other abilities to help them we should not also have to fight them for the main thing we count on to do our jobs.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;quot;rant&amp;quot;&lt;br&gt;I know rangers have it rough and can hardly survive a fight the way it is but i believe this is because we let them have our high dps weapons and frankly its like putting a gun in the hand of a child they dont know how to use them they over aggro and get themselves killed!!! They are better off playing with sticks and stones and other things you can find in the woods while hugging trees and humping bunnies. this way the worst that will happen is they will poke an eye out or break a bone with a thrown stone. Plz save the rangers further embarrassment and exp loss.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Bards bards are great we all love bards. Bards make other classes do great things and bards can do nearly anything but they have about 2 million bard only weapons and there melee is pitiful. give em a flute or something and let them go to town dont let them take weapons out of the hands of needy rogues war's and monks.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;beastlords have no impact on the game what so ever there existence is some sort of cosmic joke like berserkers.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;quot;rant off&amp;quot;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Something fun I would like to see is weapon customization even if it just came in the form of weapon dye. I know some moron will be running around with a hotpink warhammer but hey at least you know to steer clear of them when it comes time to get a group. Particle effects also would be cool. Make it costly for effects hell even make an aug slot for it and make the coolest ones drop off higher end one groupable stuff we dont want to waste raid loot on stuff like this but I think lots of people would one group for it. Customization has come a long ways since the days of eq classic when you could look at someone and tell what class and what weapons/armor they had just by looking. However at many lvls of the game everyone has the same weapon ie 1.5 and despair not just rogues but war's rng bls mnk clr brd etc etc let us change it up a bit. A flat black despair would look pretty cool let it arc some purple and blue electricity and you have an awesome looking weapon. The ability to add runes or glyphs to a blade would also be quite cool even if it were fairly limited. I realize I may have watered down my good ideas with retoric, slapshots and even a bit of bs but don't let that diminish them. Plz as always feel free to flame me im a big boy and I can cry myself to sleep with the best of them.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Jenyna&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!--   / message   --&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
