      <title>Poisons</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=roguebalance&amp;message.id=4528#M4528</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;I just finished casting my votes for the top ten and I can't help coming back to the fact that, stealth issues aside, there is almost no issue I have seen posted on these boards with regard to utility or dps or most anything else that could not be easily addresed through poisons.  (well tracking maybe, but that doesn't seem like as much a &amp;quot;need&amp;quot; as it is a &amp;quot;want&amp;quot;) It just seems like a really simple fix to me but I am neither wise nor learned in the ways of programming games...or much else really, heh.  Instead of new discs, items, skills and a whole bunch of other stuff, just make poison use more effective with stacking, standing application, (like casting spells with interrupts and all that stuff),  and improved ingredient availability.  I would also like to see some of them improved with regard to their strength and a few other issues but can live with them if they take care of the first three items I listed.  Other issues could be addressed later on but this seems like a logical first step.  Is it really that big a deal to do?  Or is it in fact something that is terribly complicated?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Just asking.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
